						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#169;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#141;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#163;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#183;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#185; (Drops) is a &amp;quot;Hide Identity + Trick Taking&amp;quot; card game where you play cards from your hand and pack the drops into boxes.&amp;#10;Boxed up drops will be shipped out if the box has the required number and colors of Drops, otherwise it will not be shipped and will be discarded. After all drops are boxed, the player that ships the most drops out of the 5 colors wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of the game, you are assigned which color drop you are in charge of. Your assigned color is not revealed until the end of the game.&amp;#10;After the game starts, in each round, one drop card will be played in order from the factory manager (start player). When playing a card, you must give priority to the colors that have not yet appeared.&amp;#10;Once everyone has played their cards, the box shipment will be determined. If the number and color of drops matches the required amount, shipping is OK. If it is more or less than what is required, it will not be shipped and discarded.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After repeating several rounds, according to the number of players, the game ends and your secret color is revealed.&amp;#10;Successfully shipped drops are counted by color, and the person with the most color wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
